    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As commented in gitter and related with the new virtual text modes (eg: [right aligned](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/11634)), it would be desireable to be able to highlight entire lines (including \"text\" after EOL). A use-case would be highlight Markdown fenced code blocks. It is possible to do it now using a regular hl such as `mkdCode` in `plasticboy/vim-markdown`, plus using a virtual text filled with spaces and using the same hl. Problem with this approach is that virtual text starts one cell after EOL, so there is a non-highlighted cell. A possible solution is to add an option to `nvim_buf_set_virtual_text` so that this additional cell is part of the virtual text. @bfredl  also commented that it may be better to have an option to change full-line highlight.",
    "closed_at": "2023-07-28T06:10:27Z",
